{"heading":"The Mosaic ordinances prefigured Christ’s ministry—Christ is the Mediator of the new covenant.","number":9,"verseCount":28,"verses":[[1,["Then verily the first ",[["covenant",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Law of Moses","tg/law-of-moses"],"."]]],["clarity-word"]]," had also ",["ordinances",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Ordinance","tg/ordinance"],"."]]]," of divine ",["service",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Service","tg/service"],"."]]],", and a worldly sanctuary."]],[2,["For there was a ",["tabernacle",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 26:1 (1–37)","ot/ex/26.1"],"; ",["39:33","ot/ex/39.33"],"."]]]," made; the first, wherein ",["was",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["candlestick",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 25:31 (31–39)","ot/ex/25.31"],"; ",["26:35","ot/ex/26.35"],"."]]],", and the ",["table",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 25:23 (23–29)","ot/ex/25.23"],"; ",["Lev. 24:6","ot/lev/24.6"],"."]]],", and the ",["shewbread",["study-note-ref","d",[["Ex. 25:30","ot/ex/25.30"],"."]]],"; which is called the sanctuary."]],[3,["And after the second ",["veil",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Jesus Christ, Types of, in Anticipation","tg/jesus-christ-types-of-in-anticipation"],"; ",["Veil","tg/veil"],"."]]],", the tabernacle which is called the ",["Holiest",["study-note-ref","b",["GR Holy of holies."]]]," of all;"]],[4,["Which had the golden censer, and the ",["ark",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Ark of the Covenant","tg/ark-of-the-covenant"],"."]]]," of the covenant overlaid round about with gold, wherein ",["was",["clarity-word"]]," the golden ",["pot",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 16:33 (33–34)","ot/ex/16.33"],"."]]]," that had manna, and ",["Aaron’s",["study-note-ref","c",[["Num. 17:10","ot/num/17.10"],"."]]]," rod that budded, and the ",["tables",["study-note-ref","d",[["Ex. 25:16 (16, 20, 40)","ot/ex/25.16"],"."]]]," of the covenant;"]],[5,["And over it the ",["cherubims",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Cherubim","tg/cherubim"],"."]]]," of glory shadowing the ",["mercyseat",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 25:17","ot/ex/25.17"],"."]]],"; of which we cannot now speak particularly."]],[6,["Now when these things were thus ",["ordained",["study-note-ref","a",["GR prepared, built."]]],", the ",["priests",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Priest, Aaronic Priesthood","tg/priest-aaronic-priesthood"],". ",["BD Priests","bd/priests"],"."]]]," went always into the first tabernacle, accomplishing the service ",["of God.",["clarity-word"]]]],[7,["But into the second ",["went",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["high priest",["study-note-ref","a",[["Heb. 9:25","nt/heb/9.25"],"; ",["10:3","nt/heb/10.3"],"."]]]," alone ",["once",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 30:10","ot/ex/30.10"],"."]]]," every year, not without blood, which he offered for himself, and ",["for",["clarity-word"]]," the errors of the people:"]],[8,["The Holy Ghost this signifying, that the way into the holiest of all was not yet made manifest, while as the first tabernacle was yet standing:"]],[9,["Which ",["was",["clarity-word"]]," a ",["figure",["study-note-ref","a",["GR similitude, type, parable. ",["TG Jesus Christ, Types of, in Anticipation","tg/jesus-christ-types-of-in-anticipation"],"."]]]," for the time then present, in which were offered both gifts and sacrifices, that could not make him that did the service ",["perfect",["study-note-ref","b",[["Heb. 7:19","nt/heb/7.19"],"."]]],", as pertaining to the conscience;"]],[10,[["Which stood",["clarity-word"]]," only in meats and drinks, and divers ",["washings",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Wash","tg/wash"],"."]]],", and ",["carnal",["study-note-ref","b",[["Heb. 7:16","nt/heb/7.16"],"."]]]," ",["ordinances",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Ordinance","tg/ordinance"],"."]]],", ",["imposed",["study-note-ref","d",[["Mosiah 13:29 (27–32)","bofm/mosiah/13.29"],"."]]]," ",["on them",["clarity-word"]]," until the time of reformation."]],[11,["But Christ being come an ",["high priest",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG High Priest, Melchizedek Priesthood","tg/high-priest-melchizedek-priesthood"],"."]]]," of good things to come, by a greater and more perfect ",["tabernacle",["study-note-ref","b",[["Mark 14:58","nt/mark/14.58"],"; ",["Heb. 8:2","nt/heb/8.2"],"."]]],", not made with hands, that is to say, not of this building;"]],[12,["Neither by the blood of goats and calves, but by his own ",["blood",["study-note-ref","a",[["Acts 20:28","nt/acts/20.28"],"; ",["Heb. 10:10","nt/heb/10.10"],"."]]]," he ",["",1530],"entered in once into the ",["holy place",["study-note-ref","b",[["Lev. 16:2 (2–4)","ot/lev/16.2"],"; ",["Heb. 10:19","nt/heb/10.19"],"."]]],", having obtained eternal ",["redemption",["study-note-ref","c",[["D&C 138:23 (18–23)","dc-testament/dc/138.23"],". ",["TG Jesus Christ, Redeemer","tg/jesus-christ-redeemer"],"; ",["Redemption","tg/redemption"],"."]]]," ",["for us.",["clarity-word"]]]],[13,["For if the ",["blood",["study-note-ref","a",[["Lev. 4:5","ot/lev/4.5"],"."]]]," of bulls and of goats, and the ashes of an heifer sprinkling the unclean, sanctifieth to the ",["purifying",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Purification","tg/purification"],"."]]]," of the flesh:"]],[14,["How much more shall the ",["blood",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Blood, Symbolism of","tg/blood-symbolism-of"],"."]]]," of Christ, who through the eternal Spirit offered himself ",["without",["study-note-ref","b",["GR blameless."]]]," ",["spot",["study-note-ref","c",[["Lev. 1:3","ot/lev/1.3"],"; ",["22:20","ot/lev/22.20"],"."]]]," to God, ",["purge",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Purification","tg/purification"],"."]]]," your ",["conscience",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Conscience","tg/conscience"],"."]]]," from dead works to serve the living God?"]],[15,["And for this cause he is the ",["mediator",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Jesus Christ, Authority of","tg/jesus-christ-authority-of"],"; ",["Jesus Christ, Mission of","tg/jesus-christ-mission-of"],"."]]]," of the ",["new",["study-note-ref","b",[["Heb. 8:13","nt/heb/8.13"],"."]]]," ",["testament",["study-note-ref","c",["JST Heb. 9:15 … covenant … (Note: JST uses “covenant” in place of “testament” in every instance in ",["vv. 15–18, 20","nt/heb/9.15,16,17,18,20"],".)"]]],", that by means of ",["death",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Jesus Christ, Death of","tg/jesus-christ-death-of"],"."]]],", for the redemption of the ",["transgressions",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Transgress","tg/transgress"],"."]]]," ",["that were",["clarity-word"]]," under the first ",["testament",["study-note-ref","f",["JST Heb. 9:15 … covenant …"]]],", they which are called might receive the ",["promise",["study-note-ref","g",[["Heb. 10:36","nt/heb/10.36"],"."]]]," of eternal ",["inheritance",["study-note-ref","h",[["D&C 137:7 (7–10)","dc-testament/dc/137.7"],". ",["TG Inheritance","tg/inheritance"],"."]]],"."]],[16,["For where a ",["testament",["study-note-ref","a",["JST Heb. 9:16 … covenant …"]]]," ",["is,",["clarity-word"]]," there must also of necessity be the ",["death",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 24:8 (3–8)","ot/ex/24.8"],"; ",["Matt. 26:28 (26–28)","nt/matt/26.28"],". ",["TG Martyrdom","tg/martyrdom"],"."]]]," of the ",["testator",["study-note-ref","c",["JST Heb. 9:16 … victim. (Note: JST uses “victim” in place of “testator” also in ",["v. 17","nt/heb/9.17"],".) ",["1 Tim. 2:5–6","nt/1-tim/2.5-6"],"; ",["D&C 135:5","dc-testament/dc/135.5"],"."]]],"."]],[17,["For a ",["testament",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Witness","tg/witness"],"."]]]," ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," of force after men are dead: ",["otherwise",["study-note-ref","b",["GR since."]]]," it is of no strength at all while the testator liveth."]],[18,["Whereupon neither the first ",["testament",["clarity-word"]]," was dedicated without blood."]],[19,["For when Moses had ",["spoken",["study-note-ref","a",[["Ex. 24:7","ot/ex/24.7"],"."]]]," every precept to all the people according to the law, he took the ",["blood",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ex. 24:6","ot/ex/24.6"],"."]]]," of calves and of goats, with water, and scarlet wool, and hyssop, and ",["sprinkled",["study-note-ref","c",[["Ex. 24:8","ot/ex/24.8"],"."]]]," both the book, and all the people,"]],[20,["Saying, This ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," the blood of the testament which God hath enjoined unto you."]],[21,["Moreover he sprinkled with blood both the tabernacle, and all the vessels of the ministry."]],[22,["And almost all things are by the law purged with blood; and without ",["shedding",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Blood, Symbolism of","tg/blood-symbolism-of"],"."]]]," of blood is no ",["remission",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Remission of Sins","tg/remission-of-sins"],"."]]],"."]],[23,[["It was",["clarity-word"]]," therefore necessary that the ",["patterns",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Symbolism","tg/symbolism"],"."]]]," of things in the heavens should be purified with these; but the heavenly things themselves with better sacrifices than these."]],[24,["For Christ is not entered into the holy places made with hands, ",["which are",["clarity-word"]]," the figures of the ",["true",["study-note-ref","a",[["Heb. 8:2","nt/heb/8.2"],"."]]],"; but into ",["heaven",["study-note-ref","b",[["Heb. 4:14","nt/heb/4.14"],"."]]]," itself, now to appear in the ",["presence",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Jesus Christ, Atonement through","tg/jesus-christ-atonement-through"],"."]]]," of God for us:"]],[25,["Nor yet that he should offer himself often, as the ",["high priest",["study-note-ref","a",[["Heb. 9:7","nt/heb/9.7"],"."]]]," entereth into the holy place every year with blood of others;"]],[26,["For then must he often have suffered since the foundation of the world: but now once ",["in",["study-note-ref","a",["JST Heb. 9:26 … in the meridian of time hath he …"]]]," the ",["end of the world",["study-note-ref","b",["GR consummation of the ages."]]]," hath he appeared to put away sin by the ",["sacrifice",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Self-Sacrifice","tg/self-sacrifice"],"."]]]," of himself."]],[27,["And as it is appointed unto men once to die, but after this the judgment:"]],[28,["So Christ was once ",["offered",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Jesus Christ, Atonement through","tg/jesus-christ-atonement-through"],"; ",["Jesus Christ, Redeemer","tg/jesus-christ-redeemer"],"; ",["Remission of Sins","tg/remission-of-sins"],"."]]]," to ",["bear",["study-note-ref","b",[["D&C 76:41","dc-testament/dc/76.41"],"."]]]," the ",["sins",["study-note-ref","c",[["Rom. 6:10","nt/rom/6.10"],"."]]]," of many; and unto them that look for him shall he ",["appear",["study-note-ref","d",[["2 Pet. 3:12","nt/2-pet/3.12"],"; ",["Rev. 1:7","nt/rev/1.7"],"."]]]," the second time without sin unto salvation."]]],"volume":"nt"}